1. Project Overview
Premium Scholars is a full-stack web platform built for university students in Kenya. It combines three distinct products into one unified experience accessible from a single account.
The Beauty Shop is a standard e-commerce store where students can browse and purchase beauty products curated specifically for the university lifestyle. Browsing is public but purchasing requires an account.
The Mentorship Program connects first-year students with verified senior students who guide them through university life. Registration is public but the portal itself is fully private. Mentor registration requires a one-time verification code issued by an administrator. Mentors and mentees are paired manually by an admin. Once paired, mentors can see their assigned mentees and mentees can see their assigned mentor.
The Requirements Shop lets first-year students order every item on their university requirements list and have it delivered to campus. Browsing is public. Ordering requires an account. The same account used for mentorship works here.
The News Board is a public-read, admin-write content feed where the Premium Scholars team posts campus updates, announcements, and program news. It appears as a scrolling ticker on every page and as a full article list at /news.

