14. News Board
Publishing
Admin publishes from the News tab. Required fields are title and body. An image is optional. On publish, the backend sanitises the body through sanitizeHtml which strips all HTML tags and script content. The image is processed by Sharp to 1200×630 WebP.
Display
The NewsBar component appears at the top of every page except the auth pages. It fetches the latest eight post titles and scrolls them left continuously using a CSS animation. Clicking any headline navigates to /news.
The /news page lists posts newest first in card format. The most recent post gets a gold left border and a Latest badge. Each card shows the full post body as whitespace-pre-wrap (preserving line breaks), author name, and formatted date.
Access Control
Reading news is fully public — no authentication required. Creating, updating, and deleting posts requires the Admin role enforced by the requireAdmin middleware on those routes.

15. WhatsApp Integration
Users can add their WhatsApp number from the profile editor, accessible via the Edit Profile button on both the mentor and mentee dashboards. The field accepts international format numbers (e.g. +254712345678). The server validates the format with a regex before saving.
Numbers are stored on the User document and are visible to:

Admin users (on the Mentors list, Users list, and mentee search results)
Mentors (on their mentee cards in the My Mentees view)
Mentees (on their assigned mentor card)

Numbers are never visible to other mentees or to the public.
Every displayed WhatsApp number is a clickable wa.me link. The format is https://wa.me/{number_without_plus}. Clicking it opens WhatsApp (web or app) with that contact pre-loaded.

16. Deployment Guide
Backend
Build the TypeScript:
bashcd backend
npm run build
The compiled output is in backend/dist/. The entry point is dist/server.js.
Run in production with PM2:
bashnpm install -g pm2
pm2 start dist/server.js --name premium-scholars-api
pm2 save
pm2 startup
Production environment variables to set:
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://...  ← MongoDB Atlas URI
JWT_SECRET=long_random_string_minimum_32_chars
JWT_EXPIRES=7d
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-domain.com
Frontend
Build the static assets:
bashcd frontend
npm run build
Output is in frontend/dist/. Serve with Nginx or deploy to Vercel, Netlify, or similar.
For Vercel or Netlify, add a redirect rule so React Router works:
/* → /index.html  (status 200)
Nginx Configuration (single server)
nginxserver {
    listen 80;
    server_name your-domain.com;

    # Serve frontend
    root /var/www/premium-scholars/frontend/dist;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }

    # Proxy API calls to backend
    location /api {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:5000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }

    # Serve uploaded files directly
    location /uploads {
        alias /var/www/premium-scholars/backend/uploads;
        expires 30d;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
    }
}
MongoDB
Use MongoDB Atlas for production. Create a cluster, get the connection string, and set it as MONGO_URI. Make sure your server's IP address is in the Atlas IP access list.

17. Known Limitations and Future Work
Payments — The order system captures delivery intent but has no payment gateway integration. The natural integration point is between the client submitting the order and the backend confirming it. Recommended: Mpesa Daraja API for Kenya, with a webhook endpoint that updates order status to confirmed on payment success.
Email notifications — No transactional emails are sent. Users have no automated confirmation when they register, place an order, or get assigned a mentor. Recommended: Resend or Postmark with triggers at user creation, order placement, and mentee assignment.
Image storage — Uploaded files are stored on the local filesystem. This works on a single server but breaks if you scale horizontally (multiple server instances cannot share a local disk) and means uploads are lost if the server is reprovisioned. Recommended: migrate to AWS S3 or Cloudflare R2 using the Multer S3 storage engine.
Real-time features — The admin dashboard and mentor dashboards require a manual refresh to see new data. There is no WebSocket layer. Recommended: Socket.io for real-time order notifications to admin and for a simple mentor-mentee messaging feature.
No get-all-mentees endpoint — By design, there is no endpoint that returns all mentees as a list. Admin can only fetch a mentee by their specific MongoDB ObjectId. This is intentional for privacy but means there is no bulk export or bulk assignment feature.
Session management — JWTs cannot be invalidated before expiry. If an admin deletes a user who is currently logged in, that user's token remains valid until it expires in seven days. Recommended: implement a token blacklist in Redis or switch to short-lived access tokens with refresh tokens.
No test suite — The project has no automated tests. Recommended: Vitest for frontend unit tests, Supertest for backend route tests, and Playwright for end-to-end tests covering the critical paths (login, place order, admin assign mentee).